{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dfbdbe27-6579-471e-8ca0-8676f23aa4f8","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x removed the VSTest compatibility layer entirely.**\n\nIn MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the default runner was already Microsoft.Testing.Platform, but a VSTest bridge was still included so `vstest.console` could discover tests. In **4.x, that bridge is gone** — `vstest.console` no longer works.\n\n### Fix: switch your CI to use `dotnet test`\n\n`dotnet test` works natively with Microsoft.Testing.Platform. No project changes needed — just replace the CI invocation:\n\n```diff\n- vstest.console MyTests.dll\n+ dotnet test MyTests.csproj\n```\n\nIf you **must** keep `vstest.console` for now, you can pin the old SDK:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n```\n\nBut the recommended path forward is to migrate off `vstest.console`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0005c4a8-89c5-4eb1-8809-97991a03842b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8 or later versions, MSTest moved to Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default runner instead of VSTest. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the VSTest compatibility layer was removed entirely.\n\nLet me explain what changed:\n\nStarting with **MSTest.Sdk 3.4+**, the default test runner switched from VSTest to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform**. In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, you could still opt back into VSTest by setting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`. However, in **MSTest.Sdk 4.0+**, the VSTest support was completely removed. \n\nThis means `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run tests built with MSTest.Sdk 4.x. To work around this, you'll need to either migrate your CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` instead, which natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform, or run the test app directly with `dotnet exec`.","outputTokens":479,"requestId":"CFC7:32055B:E1214D0:FB60710:69EC2CE8"},"id":"a4e85fc7-ccd0-4cff-8ea3-78c59477a28c","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:54:44.718Z","parentId":"ad08f291-da48-4715-8d3f-a6f0b3288629"}
